                    <span>I thoroughly enjoyed reading the book "Surely you're joking Mr. Feynman". This book is very interesting and it was very hard to put down. The many anecdotes kept me laughing and wanting more. Even though the events occurred before present day, many of the stories can still capture in intrigue of the youth of America today. This book is one of my new favorites even though the only reason I read it was for a physics project. I am happy to know that there are other books by Mr. Feynman such as "What do YOU care what other people think?". I have actually already purchased this book and cant wait to begin reading it. I enjoyed this book because not only is it science, but it is also fun science! I have never been a great admirer of the science world, but Mr. Feynman's book helped me change my entire outlook.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Melissa Robbins' Review</div>
